article.headline: Texas A&amp,M 72, Rice 60
article.story: HOUSTON -- Bryan Davis scored 18 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead Texas A&M to a 72-60 victory over Rice on Wednesday. Chinemelu Elonu added 14 points and eight rebounds for the Aggies, while Josh Carter had 11 and Donald Sloan scored 10. Texas A&M has won eight straight and is off to a 12-1 start for the second straight season. Rodney Foster, who had 18 points, was the only player to score in double figures for Rice (5-8). He was 3-of-4 from 3-point range for the Owls.
